Share this on WhatsAppSpread the love25-year-old US-based Nigerian Anesthesiologist, Shedrack Green, has drowned while swimming at a pool in Jacksonville, Florida.
It was gathered that the unfortunate incident occurred on Saturday, July 16, 2022.
According to a source, Shedrack came to America nine years ago to live the American dream. He, sadly, passed away six months after he landed a dream job in one of the best hospitals in the country.
“He rented an Airbnb apartment in Florida that has an indoor pool where he hung out with some of his friends, watching football and decided to go and swim. The CCTV showed him entering the pool and drawning. No body was around the pool at the time.
According to his close friend, shedrack has been taking swimming lessons,” the source said.
